Notes:
- Floor is a large cube flattened to 10×7 units.
- Walls are 10×4 units (height) with 0.1 thickness; pastel material.
- Student desks: 1.2×0.6 footprint, 0.6 high; chairs: 0.4×0.4 footprint, 1.0 high.
- Three rows at z​=–1.5, 0.5, 2.5; chairs placed 0.6 units behind each desk.
- Teacher desk centered at z=–2.5 with a matching chair just behind it.
- Whiteboard, bookshelf, clock, windows/curtains, plants, ceiling lights, posters, and waste bins are all positioned for clear sight lines and walking space.
- All chairs face the front (whiteboard), and no two objects overlap.

```

Notes:
- Floor is a large cube flattened to 10×7 units.
- Walls are 10×4 units (height) with 0.1 thickness; pastel material.
- Student desks: 1.2×0.6 footprint, 0.6 high; chairs: 0.4×0.4 footprint, 1.0 high.
- Three rows at z​=–1.5, 0.5, 2.5; chairs placed 0.6 units behind each desk.
- Teacher desk centered at z=–2.5 with a matching chair just behind it.
- Whiteboard, bookshelf, clock, windows/curtains, plants, ceiling lights, posters, and waste bins are all positioned for clear sight lines and walking space.
- All chairs face the front (whiteboard), and no two objects overlap.

Notes:
- Floor is a large cube flattened to 10×7 units.
- Walls are 10×4 units (height) with 0.1 thickness; pastel material.
- Student desks: 1.2×0.6 footprint, 0.6 high; chairs: 0.4×0.4 footprint, 1.0 high.
- Three rows at z​=–1.5, 0.5, 2.5; chairs placed 0.6 units behind each desk.
- Teacher desk centered at z=–2.5 with a matching chair just behind it.
- Whiteboard, bookshelf, clock, windows/curtains, plants, ceiling lights, posters, and waste bins are all positioned for clear sight lines and walking space.
- All chairs face the front (whiteboard), and no two objects overlap.

Notes:
- Floor is a large cube flattened to 10×7 units.
- Walls are 10×4 units (height) with 0.1 thickness; pastel material.
- Student desks: 1.2×0.6 footprint, 0.6 high; chairs: 0.4×0.4 footprint, 1.0 high.
- Three rows at z​=–1.5, 0.5, 2.5; chairs placed 0.6 units behind each desk.
- Teacher desk centered at z=–2.5 with a matching chair just behind it.
- Whiteboard, bookshelf, clock, windows/curtains, plants, ceiling lights, posters, and waste bins are all positioned for clear sight lines and walking space.
- All chairs face the front (whiteboard), and no two objects overlap.
